                                    <div class="margin-bottom-5">
        <h3>Fighting Information Pollution with Decision Support Systems</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="margin-bottom-10">
            <a href="/contributors/1205">Orman, Levent V</a>    </div>

<p>ABSTRACT: Information pollution is characterized as a major problem in modern organizations and in society at large. Decision support systems are proposed as the primary tool to combat information pollution. An ideal decision support system is characterized; its potential is demonstrated through examples; and a design architecture to achieve its maximum potential is proposed.</p>

    <strong>Key words and phrases: </strong>
        <a href="/keywords/39">decision support systems</a>,    <a href="/keywords/40">information pollution</a>,    <a href="/keywords/41">design architecture</a>
                                
                        
